what_failed: Regression (0.91x): Created three CTEs - filtered_dates (tiny date dimension), filtered_items (tiny item dimension), and item_avg_discount (precomputes per-item discount thresholds). Replaced correlated subquery with a join to the precomputed thresholds, eliminating row-by-row execution. Converted implicit joins to explicit JOIN syntax.
why_it_failed: Split a simple OR condition (t_hour BETWEEN 10 AND 11 OR t_hour BETWEEN 16 AND 17) into UNION ALL of two separate web_sales scans. This doubles the fact table scan. DuckDB handles same-column OR ranges efficiently in a single scan — the UNION ALL adds materialization overhead with zero selectivity benefit.
